'{"cardio":{"summary":"The primary demand is sustained aerobic output over 6-10 hours with significant elevation changes. This requires exceptional aerobic base, uphill hiking power, and fatigue resistance across varied terrain.","keyComponents":["Aerobic base development","Uphill hiking power","Sustained Zone 2 capacity","Fatigue resistance over 6+ hours","Power hiking efficiency","Downhill running control","Heart rate management on climbs","Fueling during exercise","Heat management during effort","Recovery between climb segments"],"irrelevantComponents":["Short sprint power","Anaerobic threshold intervals","Track speed","VO2 max intervals","Neuromuscular power","Lactate clearance","Explosive starts","Interval recovery","Race tactics","Kick finish"]},"strength":{"summary":"Muscular endurance is critical for maintaining form and power through repeated climbs and descents. Focus on leg durability, core stability, and anti-fatigue strength over 6-10 hours.","keyComponents":["Quad endurance for long descents","Glute power for sustained climbs","Calf endurance for technical terrain","Core stability over time","Hip flexor durability","Ankle stability on uneven ground","Anti-fatigue leg strength","Postural endurance","Eccentric quad control","Single-leg stability"],"irrelevantComponents":["Maximum strength","Power lifting","Upper body pulling","Heavy pack capacity","Overhead pressing","Grip strength","Explosive jumping","Olympic lifting","Heavy squatting","Deadlift max"]},"climbing_technical":{"summary":"Minimal technical demands but trail navigation, rock hopping, and confident footing on varied terrain are essential for safety and efficiency.","keyComponents":["Trail reading and route finding","Rock hopping confidence","Loose scree navigation","Stream crossing technique","Basic scrambling on Class 2","Foot placement precision","Balance on narrow trails","Confident descending","Weather assessment","Emergency self-rescue"],"irrelevantComponents":["Rock climbing grades","Rope work","Anchor building","Lead climbing","Multi-pitch systems","Rescue techniques","Technical crampon use","Ice axe arrest","Crevasse rescue","Alpine climbing systems"]},"flexibility":{"summary":"Hip mobility and ankle range of motion are crucial for maintaining efficient stride mechanics and preventing overuse injuries during the long event.","keyComponents":["Hip flexor mobility for stride length","Hip extension for power hiking","Ankle dorsiflexion for uphill efficiency","Calf flexibility for descents","IT band mobility","Hamstring flexibility","Dynamic hip mobility","Stride mechanics maintenance","Post-exercise recovery mobility","Injury prevention mobility"],"irrelevantComponents":["Shoulder flexibility","Thoracic spine mobility","Overhead reach","Spinal rotation","Neck mobility","Wrist flexibility","Finger flexibility","Advanced yoga poses","Extreme range of motion","Contortion-level flexibility"]}}',
'{"cardio":[{"exerciseId":"b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002","exerciseName":"Sustained Zone 2 Run","graduationTarget":"15+ miles at conversational pace","whyThisTarget":"Builds aerobic base needed for 6-10 hour sustained effort at race pace."},{"exerciseId":"b1000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003","exerciseName":"Uphill Hike with Pack","graduationTarget":"3000+ ft/hr elevation gain for 60 minutes","whyThisTarget":"Develops power hiking capacity needed for 12,000+ feet of climbing during race."}],"strength":[{"exerciseId":"b2000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002","exerciseName":"Single-Leg Step-Down","graduationTarget":"25+ controlled reps per leg","whyThisTarget":"Builds eccentric quad strength for long descents and prevents knee breakdown."},{"exerciseId":"b2000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005","exerciseName":"Push-Up Max Set","graduationTarget":"25+ unbroken reps","whyThisTarget":"Ensures core and postural endurance for maintaining form over 6-10 hours."}],"climbing_technical":[{"exerciseId":"b3000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002","exerciseName":"Scramble Confidence Assessment","graduationTarget":"3+ on confidence scale","whyThisTarget":"Adequate confidence for basic trail scrambling and rock hopping sections."}],"flexibility":[{"exerciseId":"b4000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001","exerciseName":"Deep Squat Hold","graduationTarget":"60+ seconds hold","whyThisTarget":"Ensures hip and ankle mobility for efficient stride mechanics over long distances."},{"exerciseId":"b4000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003","exerciseName":"Ankle Dorsiflexion Test","graduationTarget":"4+ inches from wall","whyThisTarget":"Adequate ankle mobility for efficient uphill stride and injury prevention."}]}',
